HEADWORD: Fud
<hw>Fud</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Of uncertain
origin.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The tail of a hare, coney, etc.</def>
<mark>[Prov. Eng. & Scot.]</mark> <rj><au>Burns.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Woolen waste, for mixing with mungo and
shoddy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fudder</ent>⟦br⟧
